<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-078-030  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 078 030.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Feb 20 1989 v6 n7 p25(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ICA members work on int'l net puzzle. (InternationalCommunications Association)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Crockett, Barton.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Attendees at the International Communications Assn's WinterSeminar say that increasing numbers of communications managers areforced to build international networks as their businesses expandabroad.andP;  Difficulties associated with building and running thesenetworks include dealing with restrictive foreign regulations, alack of adequate technology and different business norms.andP;  Mostcommunications managers claim that they are initiatinginternational networks, despite these difficulties.andP;  For example,BankAmerica Corp is cutting over high-bandwidth facilities linkingdata centers in Hong Kong and London with its domesticheadquarters.andP;  Many managers at the conference rank Latin Americaas the most hostile environment for networking because of its manypower outages and the slow service provided by carriers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     International CommunicationsNetworksConferencesInternational Communications AssociationSystem Development.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>